== Personal life ==
Bryan Adams has been a [[vegan]] for 32 years; he quit eating meat and dairy in 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.happycow.net/vegtopics/famous/bryan_adams|title=Bryan Adams is a vegan singer and songwriter|work=HappyCow}}</ref> He relayed his experiences with his plant-based diet in an interview with ''Vegan Life Magazine'' in 2016:
<blockquote>
For those people who aren't veggie or vegan it was the best gift I could ever give myself to do it. I am turning 57 years old this year and I work hard, I am always on the move but I have tons of energy because I am plant-based. It is absolutely the best thing you could ever do for yourself. It is a great path.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livekindly.co/bryan-adams-promotes-veganism-millions-fans-latest-facebook-post/|title=Bryan Adams Promotes Veganism To Millions of Fans in Latest Facebook Post|work=LiveKindly|last=Monelle|first=Jodi|date=2 December 2017}}</ref>
</blockquote>
Adams has never married. In the 1990s, he was in a relationship with Danish model [[Cecilie Thomsen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mi6.co.uk/sections/girls/thomsen.php3|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517182843/http://www.mi6.co.uk/sections/girls/thomsen.php3|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 17, 2008|title=MI6 :: The Home of James Bond 007|access-date=September 24, 2018}}</ref> Adams and Alicia Grimaldi, his former personal assistant and now trustee and co-founder of his namesake foundation, had their first daughter in April 2011 and their second daughter in February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macleans.ca/2012/04/03/straight-from-the-heart/|title=Bryan Adams still sings straight from the heart|date=April 3, 2012|publisher=Macleans.ca|access-date=June 18, 2012}}</ref> His parents are British, and one grandmother was born in Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eve.com.mt/2017/01/27/bryan-adams-the-canadian-who-came-to-malta/|title=Bryan Adams – The Canadian who came to Malta|work=Eve.com – Malta|author=Nicola Abela Garrett|date=January 27, 2017|access-date=January 28, 2017|archive-date=January 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129024242/http://www.eve.com.mt/2017/01/27/bryan-adams-the-canadian-who-came-to-malta/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Adams has homes in [[London]]<ref name="Telg3672213" /> and [[Paris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elledecor.com/celebrity-homes/articles/bryan-adams-paris-house|title=Celebrity Home Photos – Inside Luxury Celebrity Houses|publisher=Elle Decor|access-date=February 22, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121004636/http://www.elledecor.com/celebrity-homes/articles/bryan-adams-paris-house|archive-date=January 21, 2012}}</ref>

On October 30, 2021, Adams cancelled his participation in a tribute to singer [[Tina Turner]], just before the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame ceremony, after testing positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Graff |first1=Gary |title=Bryan Adams Exits Tina Turner Rock Hall Tribute After Testing Positive for COVID-19 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/music-news/bryan-adams-exits-rock-hall-tribute-covid-19-positive-1235039840/ |access-date=October 31, 2021 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=October 30, 2021}}</ref> On November 25, 2021, Adams tested positive for COVID-19 for the second time, and was placed in a hotel for a two week quarantine in Italy. {{citation needed|date=September 2022}}

== Awards and honours ==
{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Bryan Adams}}
Adams's awards and nominations include 20 [[Juno Award]]s among 56 nominations and 15 [[Grammy Award]] nominations, including a win for [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media|Best Song Written Specifically for a Motion Picture or Television]] in 1992. For his songwriting for films, Adams has been nominated for three times for [[Academy Award]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/bryan-adams-emc|title= Bryan Adams, section Honours|publisher=[[Encyclopedia of Music in Canada]]|access-date=August 23, 2019}}</ref> and five [[Golden Globe Award]]s. He was nominated for his fifth [[Golden Globe]] in 2007 for songwriting for the film ''[[Bobby (2006 film)|Bobby]]''; the song was performed by [[Aretha Franklin]] and [[Mary J. Blige]]. In 2008, Adams was ranked 38th on the list of all-time top artists in the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 50th Anniversary Charts.<ref name="BillboardAllTime" />

In 1990, Adams was awarded the [[Order of British Columbia]].<ref name=OBC>{{cite web|title=1990 Recipient: Bryan Adams – Vancouver|url=http://www.orderofbc.gov.bc.ca/members/obc-1990/1990-bryan-adams/|website=Order of British Columbia|access-date=June 28, 2014}}</ref><!-- if proponents of Order of Canada want to also add OC stuff, then add it, don't simply remove OBC mention/image --> On April 20, 1990, Adams was made a Member of the [[Order of Canada]], and on May 6, 1998, was promoted within the order to the rank of Officer of the Order of Canada.<ref>{{cite web|title=Honours Secretariat|publisher=Office of the Governor General|url=http://www.gg.ca/honour.aspx?id=2725&t=12&ln=Adams|access-date=April 12, 2016}}</ref> He received these awards for his contributions to popular music and philanthropic work via his foundation, which helps improve education for people around the world.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ipswich.gov.uk/site/scripts/news_article.php?newsID=350|title=Bryan Adams to play Ipswich Regent|publisher=Ipswich Borough Council|date=March 24, 2010|access-date=July 3, 2013|archive-date=July 3, 2013|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130703113933/http://www.ipswich.gov.uk/site/scripts/news_article.php?newsID=350|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.londonderrysentinel.co.uk/news/local/bryan_adams_tickets_to_go_on_sale_1_2098408|title=Bryan Adams tickets to go on sale|work=Londonderry Sentinel|location=UK|date=October 13, 2009|access-date=February 7, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130810043156/http://www.londonderrysentinel.co.uk/news/local/bryan_adams_tickets_to_go_on_sale_1_2098408|archive-date=August 10, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On May 1, 2010, Adams received the [[Governor General's Awards|Governor General's Performing Arts Award]] for his 30 years of contributions to the arts.<ref name="GGCA" /> On January 13, 2010, he received the [[Juno Awards of 2010|Allan Waters Humanitarian Award]] for his part in numerous charitable concerts and campaigns during his career.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://junoawards.ca/2010/01/bryan-adams-to-receive-the-allan-waters-humanitarian-award/|title=Bryan Adams Receives the Allan Waters Humanitarian Award|date=January 13, 2010|publisher=CARAS|access-date=January 16, 2010|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223102942/http://junoawards.ca/2010/01/bryan-adams-to-receive-the-allan-waters-humanitarian-award/|archive-date=February 23, 2012}}</ref>

Adams has been inducted into the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]], [[Canada's Walk of Fame]], the [[Canadian Broadcast Hall of Fame]],<ref name="Canada's Walk of Fame" /><ref name="CABHoF" /> and the [[Canadian Music Hall of Fame]].<ref name="Juno Awards" /> Adams is also a recipient of the Queen's Golden Jubilee Medal (2002) and the Queen's Diamond Jubilee Medal (2012).<ref>{{cite web|title=Honours Secretariat|publisher=Office of the Governor General|url=http://www.gg.ca/honour.aspx?id=43075&t=6&ln=Adams|access-date=April 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Honours Secretariat|publisher=Office of the Governor General|url=http://www.gg.ca/honour.aspx?id=101992&t=13&ln=Adams|access-date=April 12, 2016}}</ref> In 2015, he was awarded an [[Fellow|Honorary Fellowship]] by the [[Royal Photographic Society]] (FRPS).<ref>{{cite web |title=Honorary Fellowship |url=https://rps.org/about/awards/history-and-recipients/honorary-fellowship/ |website=The Royal Photographic Society |access-date=March 10, 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

